I"Ë<p>Cablegram 501 24 September 1940,</p>

<p>MOST SECRET</p>

<p>Repeated to Prime Minister of Canada [1], No. 2, Prime Minister of New Zealand [2], No. 17, Prime Minister of South Africa [3], No.</p>

<p>7.</p>

<p>With reference to your cablegrams Nos. 350 and 352 of 19th and 21st September respectively [4], relative to the despatch of the A.I.F. Contingent in the United Kingdom to the Middle East, His Majestyâ€™s Government in the Commonwealth of Australia has decided to form a fourth A.I.F. Division (to be designated the 9th Division) constituted as follows:-</p>

<p>(i) The contingent of A.I.F. troops in the United Kingdom to be the nucleus;</p>

<p>(ii) Units of Corps troops already formed in Australia to be utilised towards the completion of the Division, and to be replaced by further recruitment in Australia;</p>

<p>(iii) Reinforcements already existing in Australia to be sent abroad to complete the Division and to be organised as units in the Middle East.</p>

<p>In accordance with the above decision, the present objective of the strength of the A. I.F. is an Army Corps of four divisions with Corps troops.</p>

<p>A further cablegram will follow regarding the shipping requirements for convoys for the A.I.F. consequent upon the above decision.</p>

<p>MENZIES</p>

<p>_</p>

<p>1 W. L. Mackenzie King.</p>

<p>2 Peter Fraser.</p>

<p>3 Lt Gen J. C. Smuts.</p>

<p>4 On file AA:A1608, A41/1/1, xiii.</p>

